Commentary: A huge appeal for LBW and the umpire turns it down. Tim Southee and Scott Kuggeleijn decide to send it upstairs. Kuggeleijn comes from around the wicket and angles it in on a fuller length from middle, Usman Khawaja looks to flick but gets beaten onto the front pad. The replays show there was no inside edge on UltraEdge, the pitch and impact were in line but the wickets were missing as the ball was drifting down the leg stump line on Ball Tracking. Commentary: OUT! STUMPED! The introduction of spin has worked for the Kiwis as Glenn Phillips gets his first Test wicket against Australia. Phillips Tosses this one up just outside off and gets the ball to turn away a mile, Usman Khawaja shimmies down the track and looks for the big hoick against the spin but is undone. The ball gets past his outside edge and Tom Blundell collects the ball well to his left and dislodges the bails in a flash. Usman Khawaja is caught inches short of the ground as he pulls his bat back looking to get back in but does not get his bat inside the crease in the nick of time.

Commentary: A confident appeal for caught behind but turned down! Alex Carey is confident but Nathan Lyon is not so. Commentary: OUT! WHAT A GRAB! Would you believe it? Travis Head has struck with his third ball. An inspired bowling change from Pat Cummins and this is a stunning catch from Steven Smith. Head stays over the wicket and pushes it through, full and around off, Will Young plays for the ball turning into him and pushes at it with hard hands. Young could have left it if he would have wanted to but he decides to play at it. Gets an outside edge that goes quickly to the left of first slip. Steven Smith stays low and his sharp reflexes comes to his rescue as he pulls off a low one-handed stunner near his ankle.
